  "prompt": "If I connect USB OTG pendrive to my power bank and connect the other point with data cable to my mobile, will pendrive be working on my mobile?",
  "response": "Connecting a USB OTG (On-The-Go) pendrive to your mobile device using a power bank as an intermediary will not work as intended. Here's why:\n\n1. **USB OTG Functionality**: USB OTG allows a mobile device to act as a host, enabling it to read data from USB devices like pendrives. For this functionality, the OTG cable typically connects directly between the mobile device and the pendrive.\n\n2. **Power Bank Role**: A power bank is designed to supply power to devices and does not facilitate data transfer. It lacks USB host capabilities that are needed for OTG functionality.\n\n3. **Proper Connection**: To use a USB OTG pendrive with your mobile, connect the pendrive directly to the mobile device using an appropriate OTG adapter or cable. Ensure your mobile device supports OTG and that the requisite OTG setting is enabled if necessary.\n\nIn summary, bypassing the power bank is necessary for the USB OTG pendrive to work with your mobile device. Connect the pendrive directly to the mobile via an OTG cable for data transfer.",
